Text: Gah! What's going on here?!

The intruder took out the security ghost and
head guard!

Where did she run off to? She couldn't have
gotten far.

Good instincts. I wouldn't say any of those guards
were incompetent.

Still, if you think such a team could beat anyone,
no matter who, well...
...I wouldn't be so sure about that.
I think I'll just relax a bit while things cool down.
Well, now...
Huh?!
Out on a moonlit walk so late at night?
(Wh-What the?!)
(What is she doing out here at this time of night?)

(And I didn't sense her presence. She must be
masking herself to sneak up on me.)
(Which means...she knows I'm the intruder! Not good!)

Please, don't look so upset. You attended the sermon
today, didn't you?
(She's good. She's no simple prophet.)

(She's clearly had combat training, and more than
the Church paladins, I'd bet.)
My my, you're a feisty little kitten.
You saw my face, so I can't let you live.
I, did not see you.
But, you saw me. Just like earlier today...
What?!
There she is! ...Your Holiness?!
You! Get away from the prophet!
Damn!
Silence! And put away your sword!
What?!

She is my friend. Leave us immediately and return
to your duties.
But, Your Holiness!

My words are not merely my own. They come from
the goddess herself.
Harming her is tantamount to harming the goddess.

But, she drew her blade on you! And you say she is
no danger?
Indeed. She is my friend. She will not harm me.

Forgive me, Your Holiness. I will do as the
goddess wishes. Bandits are roaming about,
so please be careful.

I shall, thank you. May the blessings of the goddess
be on you.
What are you up to?!

I am not up to anything. It is as I said.
Our meeting is the will of the goddess.
And do you think I'm going to buy that?

The prophecies that are shared with us are the will
of the goddess and are far beyond mortal minds.

So all this nonsense about me being your friend is
some sign from your gracious Beatrix, then?
Yes, precisely.

(Has she got something up her sleeve? Or is this
what true faith looks like?)

And if I took your head off your shoulders, would
that also be the goddess's will?
No, that could not be.
Hah! I didn't think soâ€”

No, that is not what I mean. I am saying that,
as my friend, you would never take my head.

For, despite many opportunities even up to this
moment, you have not done so.
Don't think I won't!
(Why did I back off?! And at the same pace she did!)

(I see. She's just too good. That paladin knew it,
and that's why he left when she told him to.)
...I am certain that we will meet again.
I would prefer not to.
However, our individual wishes matter notâ€¦
...Damn!
The will of the goddess will bring us together again.
And, so, just like that they discovered me.

Wow. That's a crazy story. It's not like you to get
spotted, Zeta.

And then she goes and treats me like a friend and
lets me go! I don't get it, it's just humiliating!

Um, even monkeys fall from trees? Even dogs bark up
the wrong tree?
Hey! I'm not a monkey or a dog!
True...

(She's a bit of a goof, but also kind of a genius.
The world is bigger than I thought, if there's
someone out there who can outwit Zeta.)

(Don't let it get to you, Zeta. It's just the
universe teaching you a lesson.)

I was trying to copy you, my lord, and pretend to be
a regular person.

Heh! Well, would you like to learn the secrets of
lurking in the shadows?
Are there any?! If you'll teach me, then please!
Umm...

When you're at a concert...I mean, at a public event,
pretending you don't care actually draws attention.

The people on stage and those around you will think,
"If you don't care, why are you here?"
Ah!

Now that I think about my attitude there, it was a
lot like a foreigner trying to blend in.
That's it. Now, try this.
...Cross my arms and bob my head?

Do this casually, standing as far back as possible.
I call this Shadow Wisdom, "Low Profile Fan Face."
Low Profile Fan Face...?!

It creates a quiet attitude of mental superiority,
like you know more than anyone else about
who's on stage.

This kind of attitude makes those around you think,
"Yeah, another one of those people," so everyone
thinks the same thing about you.

Even if there's no basis for it! You're really
just another member of the audience, like
everyone else.

But you can't help acting like something special.
It's a way to seem like a totally normal person.

Now that you mention it, I did notice the same
thing there.

There were tons of people there with a face like,
"I know the prophet better than anyone!"
I've got a long way to go...
Heh. Just keep at it.
...I know my lord better than anyone!

Yes! Just like that. That's a perfect Low Profile
Fan Face.
But I really do want to know you...
Hahah, you're good! You're a quick study, Zeta.
